WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'OctiX' is played on an 'X'-shaped board. The idea is to line 5
tiles or more with the same pattern, either horizontally or
diagonally. The more tiles you line up, the more points you get.
When a series of 5 or more tiles is made up, the entire lineup is
removed.

  Each time you move a tile and it doesn't make a series of at
least 5 similar tiles, 3 more tiles are randomly placed on the
board. If one of these tiles creates a series of 5 or more similar
tiles, that series will be removed from the board, but you will
get no points.

  Be careful not to let the board fill up completely because when
that happens, the game is over.

  Have fun!

